{"questionId":"9072654","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the difference between the speed of light corresponding to these two wavelengths in the core glass.</span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"v = \\frac{c}{n} = {v_{1299}} = \\frac{{2.99792 \\times {{10}^8}}}{{1.45061}} = 2.06666 \\times {10^8}\">\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>c</mi>\n    <mi>n</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>1299</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.99792</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>8</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.45061</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.06666</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> «ms<sup>–1</sup>» <em><strong>AND</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{v_{1301}} = \\frac{{2.99792 \\times 10{}^8}}{{1.45059}} = 2.06669 \\times {10^8}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>v</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>1301</mn>\n      </mrow>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.99792</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>8</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1.45059</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.06669</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>«ms<sup>–1</sup>»</span></span></p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta v = \\left( {\\frac{1}{{1.45059}} - \\frac{1}{{1.45061}}} \\right) \\times 2.99792 \\times {10^8}\">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1.45059</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>1.45061</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>2.99792</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mn>8</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> &nbsp;✔</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\Delta v = 2.85 \\times {10^3}\">\n  <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi>\n  <mi>v</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.85</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> <em><strong>OR</strong></em>&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3 \\times {10^3}\">\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>10</mn>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>«ms<sup><span style=\"font-size:small;\">–1</span></sup>»✔</span></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9072654","referenceCode":"19M.3.SL.TZ2.12bi","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Determine the difference between the speed of light corresponding to these two wavelengths in the core glass.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"bi","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 4: Waves","4.4 – Wave behaviour","Core","Topic 4: Waves"],"membe